rf Bug I hope</span><hr size=1> When I read the change to damage adds in the that went live it sure sounded like it was done only to prevent people from giving level 50 dmg adds to level 5 players to powerlevel them faster and also to lessen their necessity in epic purple con monster fights. I was in the tuscaran glacier and fighting purple cons with a group of 25 or so mids. I hit the epic monsters for 4 damage with my axe, and +4 damage add. So seems to me that damage add caps at your weapon damage now no matter what DPS add you have. Thus if you style, your damage add will raise, this is a bigger nerf for all those classes who can't style and still try to take benefit from the damage adds. And pretty much makes me want to lower my battlesong skill down so I will still hit for 4 damage +4 damage add bonus with a lower level damage add, so there is no point to raising my skill to get the higher one. Of course this is all from an epic monster PvE point of view. When most level 50's just concern themselves with RvR. So lets look at RvR.<br>
<br>
Thanes tell me their 9 DPS damage add is doing about 43 % less damage than it used to vs even con level 50's. I was fighting an albion merc and he was hitting me for 31 dmg add per swing with his fast 1h swords. I hit back with my 2h arc war cleaver which is speed 5.3 and my chant of blood did 34 damage add which normally would do about 60 damage add. I know when you style you damage add lowers but I always did 50-60 damage add even when i DID style with my 2h cleaver. <br>
Looks like Damage adds nerfed across the boards. This is a real annoyance which I hope is a bug. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
